dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
dcterms:description: A dataset containing 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 different classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
dcterms:description: A dataset containing 60,000 32x32 color images in 100 different classes, with 600 images per class. It is used for more fine-grained image classification tasks compared to CIFAR-10.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100

dcterms:description: A large-scale dataset with over 14 million images labeled across 20,000 categories. It is widely used for training deep learning models in image classification and object detection tasks.
dcterms:title: ImageNet

dcterms:description: A smaller version of the ImageNet dataset, designed for quick experiments and testing. It contains a subset of images from the original ImageNet dataset.
dcterms:title: ImageNet-tiny
